Food offered up could range from their staple of [[rice]], to seafood, food foraged from the mountains, seasonal foods, local specialties, or food connected to the enshrined deity. At the end of the ritual, the offered food is eaten together to gain a sense of unity with the kami, and to gain their blessing and protection. The rite is known as ''naorai.''
